parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor can cause the airbag light to stay on, potentially leading to a failure to deploy in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: the airbag sensor light comes on for no reason

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and damage to property.
symptoms: even when the brake is depressed
the vehicle lunges forward or into reverse without assistance
the vehicle accelerates rapidly without input from the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear seat belts can lead to entrapment, difficulty in exiting the vehicle, and potentially life-threatening situations in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The rear seat belts fail to retract
the rear seat belts become shredded
the rear seat belts latch and cannot be unlatched
the rear seat belts trap occupants
the rear seat belts will not release.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake wear and failure can lead to a loss of braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents and compromising the safety of the driver and passengers.
symptoms: grinding or screeching noise when applying the brakes
shuttering or jerking sensation when braking.
